HEADWORD: Impolicy
<hw>Im*pol"i*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of
being impolitic; inexpedience; unsuitableness to the end proposed; bad
policy; <as>as, the <ex>impolicy</ex> of fraud</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Horsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impolite</ent>⟦br⟧
